Package: suest
Title: Seemingly Unrelated Estimation for Comparing Model Predictions and Effects
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R:
    person("Trenton D.", "Mize", email = "tmize@purdue.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Combines two separately fitted cross-sectional regression models
    using seemingly unrelated estimation and constructs a joint model-robust
    covariance matrix from observation-level score contributions. The combined
    object integrates with 'marginaleffects' to compare predictions, slopes,
    and average comparisons across models. Implements the general framework in
    Mize, Doan, and Long (2019) <doi:10.1177/0081175019852763>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
